    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-11T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="11"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1146a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-11T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 11, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>907. Please endeavor to obtain from the same source which supplied comments at
                    end of your cablegram 1656 of November 19, <pb facs="0116" n="24" xml:id="pg_24"
                    /> 1917,<note n="1" xml:id="d11fn1">
                        <persName>Kurt Hahn</persName>, German Liberal leader; see <ref
                            target="frus1917Supp02v01#pg_311">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, Supplement 2, vol. I,
                            pp. 311</ref>–<ref target="frus1917Supp02v01#pg_316">316</ref>.</note>
                    and illuminating statement enclosed with mail despatch 334 of November 27,<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d11fn2">Not printed.</note> an account of the reaction of the
                    German Liberals to the President’s statement of peace terms. Reply by cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
